        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-03T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-03T20:00:00-05:00" n="712" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d712">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.52/2–2847: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Spain</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-03T20:00:00-05:00">March 3, 1947—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>194. We are wholly in accord with prompt action you took <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 166 Feb 28. You are authorized to take
                    such further measures in this connection as you deem appropriate, including
                    request for public retraction of references to Asst Sec Braden.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
